This is Perl module Task::BeLike::PUNYTAN.

INSTALLATION

Task::BeLike::PUNYTAN installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is set up,
you should just be able to do

    % cpan Task::BeLike::PUNYTAN

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

DOCUMENTATION

Task::BeLike::PUNYTAN documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc Task::BeLike::PUNYTAN

To read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

punytan
